          <div class="ae-row"><div class="ae-left"><span class="ae-val neutral">48.0%</span><div class="ae-bar neutral" style="width:73.4%;"></div></div><div class="ae-center">Hypertension</div><div class="ae-right"><div class="ae-bar accent" style="width:5.7%;min-width:4px;"></div><span class="ae-val accent">3.7%</span></div></div>
          <div class="ae-row"><div class="ae-left"><span class="ae-val neutral">14.5%</span><div class="ae-bar neutral" style="width:22.2%;"></div></div><div class="ae-center">Vomiting</div><div class="ae-right"><div class="ae-bar accent" style="width:2.9%;min-width:4px;"></div><span class="ae-val accent">1.9%</span></div></div>
          <div class="ae-row"><div class="ae-left"><span class="ae-val neutral">12.7%</span><div class="ae-bar neutral" style="width:19.4%;"></div></div><div class="ae-center">Nausea</div><div class="ae-right"><div class="ae-bar accent" style="width:5.7%;min-width:4px;"></div><span class="ae-val accent">3.7%</span></div></div>
          <div class="ae-row"><div class="ae-left"><span class="ae-val neutral">10.4%</span><div class="ae-bar neutral" style="width:15.9%;"></div></div><div class="ae-center">Bradycardia</div><div class="ae-right"><div class="ae-bar accent" style="width:0%;min-width:2px;"></div><span class="ae-val accent">0%</span></div></div>
          <div class="ae-row"><div class="ae-left"><span class="ae-val neutral">5.2%</span><div class="ae-bar neutral" style="width:8%;"></div></div><div class="ae-center">Fever</div><div class="ae-right"><div class="ae-bar accent" style="width:0%;min-width:2px;"></div><span class="ae-val accent">0%</span></div></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>Development Pipeline</h2>
      <h3>Long COVID / Post-COVID Syndrome</h3>
      <p>Phase II clinical trial completed in 2024. REGENECYTE received FDA Regenerative Medicine Advanced Therapy (RMAT) designation for Long COVID. Expanded Access program clearance received in 2026. Results published in peer-reviewed literature (NCT05682560).</p>
      <h3>Acute Ischemic Stroke</h3>
      <p>Phase I clinical trial results evaluating cord blood therapy for acute ischemic stroke were published in the Tzu Chi Medical Journal in 2025.</p>
      <h3>Spinal Cord Injury</h3>
      <p>StemCyte-sponsored clinical trial for spinal cord injury (MC001) is active.</p>

      <h2>Mechanism of Action</h2>
      <p>Hematopoietic stem/progenitor cells from REGENECYTE migrate to the bone marrow where they divide and mature. The mature cells are released into the bloodstream, partially or fully restoring blood counts and immune function.</p>
      <p>In patients with enzymatic abnormalities due to certain severe storage disorders, mature leukocytes from transplantation may synthesize enzymes that circulate and improve cellular functions of native tissues.</p>

      <h2>Dosage &amp; Administration</h2>
      <p>For intravenous use only. Do not irradiate. The recommended minimum dose is 2.5 &times; 10&#x2077; nucleated cells/kg at cryopreservation. Matching for at least 4 of 6 HLA-A, HLA-B, and HLA-DRB1 alleles is recommended. Infuse over 15 to 60 minutes. Monitor the patient during and for at least six hours after administration.</p>

      <p class="source" style="margin-top:48px;">All clinical data from <a href="https://www.fda.gov/media/183744/download?attachment" target="_blank">FDA Full Prescribing Information &mdash; REGENECYTE (HPC, Cord Blood), BLA 125764/0</a>.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SIDEBAR -->
